  faqs={[
    { question: "How do I check my PESCO bill online in March 2026?", answer: "Enter your 14-digit PESCO reference number in the bill checker above and click Check Bill. Your complete PESCO electricity bill appears in seconds with amount, due date, and all charges. Free, no login, works 24/7 for all KPK districts." },
    { question: "What is the difference between PESCO and TESCO?", answer: "PESCO covers settled districts of KPK: Peshawar, Mardan, Swat, Abbottabad, Kohat, Bannu, D.I. Khan, and others. TESCO covers the Merged Tribal Districts (formerly FATA): Khyber, Kurram, Bajaur, Mohmand, North Waziristan, South Waziristan, and Orakzai. Check your bill heading to confirm which company supplies your area." },
    { question: "What are PESCO winter peak hours?", answer: "PESCO winter peak hours (November to March) are 5:00 PM to 9:00 PM — one full hour earlier than other DISCOs which use 6:00–10:00 PM. This reflects KPK's earlier winter darkness. Avoid running heavy appliances between 5 PM and 9 PM in winter to save on per-unit charges." },
    { question: "How do I check PESCO bill for Swat?", answer: "Swat is within PESCO's service area. Enter your 14-digit PESCO reference number in the checker above — it works for all PESCO districts including Swat, Mingora, Matta, and Bahrain. Swat is one of PESCO's highest-tourism districts, and PESCO provides electricity to all major Swat hotels, resorts, and residential areas." },
    { question: "How do I check PESCO bill for Abbottabad?", answer: "Abbottabad is covered by PESCO's Hazara Division circle. Enter your 14-digit reference number in the checker above. Abbottabad, Havelian, Harippur, and Mansehra all fall under PESCO. Hazara division is known for relatively mild climate — most consumers here can maintain Protected status without major lifestyle changes." },
    { question: "How do I download my PESCO duplicate bill?", answer: "After the bill loads, click Download PDF and select Save as PDF in the print dialog. Your PESCO duplicate bill saves instantly — ready for payment at a JazzCash shop or bank in Peshawar, Mardan, Swat, or anywhere in KPK." },
    { question: "How do I pay my PESCO bill online in KPK?", answer: "Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, or any bank app. Select Electricity, choose PESCO or WAPDA, enter your 14-digit reference number, and confirm. JazzCash has the widest agent network in KPK for cash payments. Easypaisa is also widely available in Peshawar, Mardan, and Swat." },
    { question: "Why does PESCO have more load shedding than LESCO?", answer: "PESCO's service area has higher transmission and distribution losses compared to urban Punjab DISCOs. More rural areas, longer lines, and historically lower bill recovery rates contribute to higher load shedding durations. Urban Peshawar typically sees 4–8 hours of load shedding; rural KPK areas can see 12–18 hours. Regular bill payment by consumers in your feeder area directly reduces your load shedding." },
    { question: "What is the grace period for PESCO bill payment?", answer: "PESCO gives 7 days after the due date to pay without a late payment surcharge. After 7 days, a 10% surcharge applies. In remote KPK areas where paper bills arrive late, check your due date online using this tool before the deadline." },
    { question: "How do I file a billing complaint with PESCO?", answer: "Call 118 or 091-9213205 with your reference number. Get a CRN. PESCO must resolve within 14 working days. Escalate to NEPRA at 0800-63000 if ignored. Visit your nearest PESCO subdivision office in Peshawar, Mardan, Abbottabad, or your city for complex disputes." },
